developing for Google Chrome.

00:04:55.850 --> 00:04:58.050
And so we have full screen
apps running

00:04:58.050 --> 00:04:59.610
right in the browser.

00:04:59.610 --> 00:05:03.310
And honestly, with that,
capabilities for us to be able

00:05:03.310 --> 00:05:06.370
to develop locally on our
computers and have it run

00:05:06.370 --> 00:05:10.820
almost identically on the TV,
was just great for us.

00:05:10.820 --> 00:05:13.460
So there wasn't a whole
lot of issues there.

00:05:13.460 --> 00:05:16.680
Obviously we've gone through a
couple of iterations of speed

00:05:16.680 --> 00:05:19.970
and things like that, and just
working out some of the kinks

00:05:19.970 --> 00:05:20.470
internally.

00:05:20.470 --> 00:05:23.100
But for us it really hasn't
been a problem at all.

00:05:23.100 --> 00:05:25.675
Now when we go to native
applications, one of the takes

00:05:25.675 --> 00:05:29.690
