add anything else to it.

00:14:37.710 --> 00:14:41.830
But what MOVL does is really
take advantage of the TV and

00:14:41.830 --> 00:14:43.020
the second screen experience.

00:14:43.020 --> 00:14:46.620
So we're all about everybody
around the living room using

00:14:46.620 --> 00:14:49.430
their mobile devices, their
tablets, to interact together

00:14:49.430 --> 00:14:52.860
in a social experience where
the TV is the anchor point,

00:14:52.860 --> 00:14:55.070
whether that's in a living room
at home, or it might be

00:14:55.070 --> 00:14:59.180
in a bar in a restaurant, that
people can actually use this

00:14:59.180 --> 00:15:01.880
TV and the mobile devices in a
really social way to have a

00:15:01.880 --> 00:15:03.420
lot of fun, entertainment-based

00:15:03.420 --> 00:15:04.330
applications.

00:15:04.330 --> 00:15:07.710
So for us, that's the best thing
about developing for TV,

00:15:07.710 --> 00:15:11.060
